job_description:
Summary of day-to-day responsibilities:
Looking for a Cloud Software Engineer to assist with data transfers from legacy sources to GCP using Dataflow/Airflow/Apache Beam either batch or streaming.
Responsibilities:
• Responsible for developing and maintaining software applications in a cloud-based environment;
• Design, develop, test, and deploy cloud-based applications that meet the needs of customers and stakeholders;
• Collaborate with other engineers and stakeholders to ensure that applications are scalable, secure, and reliable;
• Collaborate with the data engineering team to integrate data pipeline code into CI/CD processes (GITLAB).
Must Have: 
• Hands-on experience with data integration tools and technologies such as Google Dataflow, AirFlow, Apache Beam, or equivalent;
• Experience with deploying and managing Big Data solutions on GCP, both batch and real-time;
• Experience with GCP's infrastructure-as-code tools, particularly Terraform, to provision and configure cloud resources;
• Knowledge of networking components (VPC, subnets, firewall rules) for secure communication;
• Strong programming skills in Python.
